    {
      "id": "node-class-demo-reader",
      "type": "port",
      "label": "Reader",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -700,
        "y": -380
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "view": {
          "intent": "node",
          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "markdown": "# Node Class Demo\n\nThis graph keeps the lesson deliberately small. Import the canonical `node` class through a bridge, inspect the class artifact, then create a local instance yourself. The point is not magic. The point is that a class gives you a reusable starter contract."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "node-class-demo-intro",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "What This Demo Proves",
      "root": true,
      "position": {
        "x": -1180,
        "y": -20
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## What this demo proves\n\nA node class is not a mysterious runtime-only thing.\n\n- the class is just another graph artifact\n- the bridge gives your graph authority to create from it\n- the created node is still a local node in your graph\n- the class simply supplies starter defaults and views"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "node-class-demo-bridge",
      "type": "bridge",
      "label": "Node Class Bridge",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -560,
        "y": -10
      },
      "width": 340,
      "height": 150,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "memo": "Import the canonical node class. Press CREATE when you are ready to make a local instance.",
        "intent": "external",
        "resourceKind": "node-class",
        "scope": "focused-graph",
        "grants": [
          "create"
        ],
        "authority": "bridge",
        "bridge": {
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/node.node-class.node",
          "resourceKind": "node-class",
          "scope": "focused-graph",
          "grants": [
            "create"
          ]
        },
        "target": {
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/node.node-class.node",
          "mode": "bridge",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "resourceKind": "node-class",
          "scope": "focused-graph",
          "grants": [
            "create"
          ],
          "label": "Node Class",
          "key": "node"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "node-class-demo-class-notes",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "What The Class Supplies",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -20,
        "y": -40
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## What the class supplies\n\nThe canonical `node` class gives a created instance:\n\n- a starter label\n- a starter size\n- starter data fields like `title`, `body`, and `status`\n- authored views such as detail, summary, icon, and editor\n\nThe instance still belongs to the current graph. After creation, edit the local node like any other node."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "node-class-demo-open-class",
      "type": "portal",
      "label": "Open Class Artifact",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 520,
        "y": -20
      },
      "width": 300,
      "height": 180,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
