    },
    {
      "id": "node-class-demo-practice",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Try It",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -1180,
        "y": 380
      },
      "width": 480,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Try it\n\n1. Use the bridge's `CREATE` action.\n2. Select the new local node on the canvas.\n3. Change `title`, `body`, or `status` in properties.\n4. Observe that you are editing a local node instance, not rewriting the class artifact.\n\nIf you want to inspect the authored source of truth, open the class artifact from the portal."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "node-class-demo-checkpoint",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Checkpoint",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -560,
        "y": 400
      },
      "width": 460,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Checkpoint\n\nYou are done when you can say:\n\n- this graph imported the class through a bridge\n- the class itself lives in its own graph artifact\n- the created node is local to the current graph\n- classes provide starter law and starter views, not ownership of the instance"
      }
    },
